# Raycast Extension Guidelines

## Store Requirements

- `name` must be lowercase hyphenated (URL-compatible); `title` is the human-readable Store/preferences label
- `description` (extension-level) must be one clear sentence stating what the extension does; shown in Store listing
- Every command must have a non-empty `description`
- `author` must exactly match the Raycast account username
- `license` must be `"MIT"`
- `categories` are **Title Case**, case-sensitive; must include at least one valid category:
  `Applications`, `Communication`, `Data`, `Documentation`, `Design Tools`, `Developer Tools`, `Finance`, `Fun`, `Media`, `News`, `Productivity`, `Security`, `System`, `Web`, `Other`
- Icon: 512×512 px PNG named `extension-icon.png` (or `extension-icon@dark.png` for dark variant); extensions using the default Raycast icon are **rejected**
- Remove unused assets from the `assets/` folder before submission
- `README.md` is required if the extension needs setup (API tokens, non-trivial config); placed in the extension root
- `package-lock.json` must be committed; use `npm` (not yarn/pnpm) for dependencies
- Run `npm run build` and verify the dist build works before opening a PR
- No external analytics — using third-party tracking SDKs causes rejection
- No Keychain access requests — use Raycast preferences API for credentials instead

## Naming Conventions

- Extension and command **titles** follow Apple Style Guide (Title Case): ✅ `Search Contacts` ❌ `search contacts`, `SEARCH CONTACTS`
- Command titles: prefer `<Verb> <Noun>` structure; avoid articles (`Search Emoji` not `Search an Emoji`)
- Extension title: use nouns over verbs; be specific if single-command (`Apple Contacts Search` not just `Contacts`)
- Lowercase is acceptable for canonically lowercase trademarks: `npm`, `iOS`, `macOS`

## Action Panel Rules

- Action titles use **Title Case**: ✅ `Copy Phone Number`, `Open in Contacts` ❌ `copy phone`, `Set priority`
- The **first** action is the primary action (triggered by `↵`) — put the most useful action first
- The **second** action is secondary (triggered by `⌘↵`)
- Destructive actions **must** use `Action.Style.Destructive` and show a confirmation dialog (`confirmAlert`) before executing
- Add `…` suffix to actions that open a submenu: ✅ `Set Priority…`; submenu items should not repeat the parent name
- Provide icons for actions when other actions in the same panel have icons (avoid mixed icon/no-icon lists)
- Group related actions with `ActionPanel.Section`

## Keyboard Shortcuts

- Do **not** conflict with Raycast system shortcuts: `⌘K` (action panel), `⌘P` (no-view command), `⌘,` (preferences), `⇧,` (configure command), `⇧D` (disable command)
- Custom shortcuts on primary/secondary actions won't display in the UI — document them in README if non-obvious

## UX Conventions

- Use `keepPreviousData: true` on `useCachedPromise` to avoid flickering when reloading data
- Never render an empty list before data arrives — show the loading indicator instead to avoid flickering "No results"
- Always handle errors: use `failureToastOptions` on `useCachedPromise` or call `showToast` with `Toast.Style.Failure`
- Do **not** set `navigationTitle` on the root command (Raycast sets it automatically to the command name); only set it on nested screens
- Use `List.EmptyView` / `Grid.EmptyView` to customise the empty state
- Use the Raycast Navigation API (`pushToHistory`, `push`) — don't implement a custom navigation stack
- Add `placeholder` to all search bars and text fields

## Code Rules

- **No `console.log`** in production code — use Raycast's `showToast` or `showHUD` for user-facing feedback
- Use `@raycast/api` imports only; do not bundle heavy binary dependencies
- Request only the macOS permissions the extension actually needs
- Use the Raycast preferences API for all user-configurable settings and credentials; do not build separate config commands

## package.json Requirements

```jsonc
{
  "name": "lowercase-hyphenated",        // URL-compatible, unique
  "title": "Human Readable Title",       // Title Case, Store-facing
  "description": "One sentence.",        // Required, shown in Store
  "icon": "extension-icon.png",          // 512×512 PNG in assets/
  "author": "raycast-username",          // Must match Raycast account
  "license": "MIT",
  "categories": ["Productivity"],        // Title Case, at least one
  "commands": [
    {
      "name": "command-slug",
      "title": "Command Title",          // Title Case
      "description": "What it does.",    // Required
      "mode": "view"
    }
  ]
}
```
